<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='343733' id='t-343733'>I go to the concept of &quot;The Lion King&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='346264' id='t-346264'>and I say, &quot;What is the essence of it?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='348332' id='t-348332'>What is the abstraction?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='349968' id='t-349968'>If I were to reduce this entire story</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='353229' id='t-353229'>into one image, what would it be?&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='355970' id='t-355970'>The circle. The circle. It's so obvious.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='358924' id='t-358924'>The circle of life. The
circle of Mufasa's mask.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='362901' id='t-362901'>The circle that, when we come
